# Gap 1 – Clinical Escalation Protocol & PHC Feedback Loop

## 1.1 The Missing Loop

The original plan documents referrals but does not define what happens after. Without a structured feedback pathway, the system cannot improve from real-world outcomes and longitudinal claims about trajectory cannot be validated.

The required loop is:

```
SCREENING (AWW)
     │
     ▼
RISK FLAG: High / Critical
     │
     ▼
REFERRAL RECORD CREATED (AWW logs referral in app → syncs to server)
     │
     ▼
PHC / SPECIALIST VISIT (offline event — ground truth is generated here)
     │
     ▼
OUTCOME CAPTURE (two pathways):
  A) AWW records PHC outcome in app (low-tech: outcome code dropdown)
  B) PHC MIS integration (if available — state-dependent)
     │
     ▼
OUTCOME STORED IN `referral_outcomes` TABLE
     │
     ▼
GROUND TRUTH PIPELINE: outcome → training label ingestion → model retraining
```

## 1.2 Database Addition: `referral_outcomes`

```sql
referral_id         UUID PRIMARY KEY
assessment_id       UUID                  -- FK to assessments
child_id            UUID
referral_date       DATE
referred_to         VARCHAR(100)          -- e.g., "PHC Khandwa Block 2"
referral_type       VARCHAR(50)           -- 'NRC', 'PHC_OPD', 'SPECIALIST', 'ANGANWADI_FOLLOWUP'
outcome_capture_method VARCHAR(20)        -- 'AWW_INPUT', 'PHC_API', 'SUPERVISOR_CONFIRM'
outcome_date        DATE
outcome_code        SMALLINT
  -- 0 = Not attended
  -- 1 = Attended; no concern found
  -- 2 = Attended; mild concern; home management
  -- 3 = Attended; moderate concern; follow-up required
  -- 4 = Attended; significant delay confirmed; intervention initiated
outcome_notes       TEXT                  -- Optional free-text
confirmed_by        UUID                  -- Supervisor who verified
recorded_at         TIMESTAMPTZ
```

## 1.3 Outcome Quality Scoring

Not all outcomes are equally reliable for model training:

| Outcome Method | Quality Score | Used for Retraining? |
|---|---|---|
| PHC electronic record (API) | 1.0 | Yes |
| Supervisor-confirmed AWW input | 0.85 | Yes |
| AWW self-reported (unverified) | 0.50 | Only if volume low; flagged |
| Not attended (no outcome) | 0.0 | Excluded |

Only outcomes with quality score ≥ 0.5 are included in the retraining dataset. All outcomes are stored regardless.

## 1.4 Ground Truth Pipeline (Post-Pilot)

After Phase 7 pilot, if ≥ 100 confirmed outcomes are collected:

1. Extract `(assessment_features, outcome_code ≥ 3)` as positive labels
2. Extract `(assessment_features, outcome_code ≤ 1)` as negative labels
3. Weight samples by `quality_score`
4. Feed into the Phase 2 retraining pipeline as `real_world_v1` dataset
5. Compare AUC-ROC against `synthetic_v1` model
6. Publish Model Card v2.0 with real vs synthetic performance comparison

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Until ≥ 100 validated outcomes are collected, the model must be labelled in all outputs as: **"Trained on validated synthetic data; real-world calibration pending."** This is both accurate and required for intellectual honesty during Demo Day review.

## 1.5 API Additions

| Method | Endpoint | Role | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/v1/referrals` | AWW | Create referral record for High/Critical child |
| PATCH | `/api/v1/referrals/{id}/outcome` | AWW, Supervisor | Record PHC outcome |
| GET | `/api/v1/referrals/child/{child_id}` | Supervisor | Full referral + outcome history |
| GET | `/api/v1/referrals/analytics` | CDPO, State | Referral completion rate, outcome distribution |

