# Gap 3 – Workload Impact Model

## 3.1 Time-Motion Estimate (Per Child, Per Screening Session)

This estimate must be presented to government reviewers to answer: *"Does this increase AWW workload?"*

| Activity | Time (New System) | Time (Baseline, Paper) | Delta |
|---|---|---|---|
| Child record lookup or new registration | 1.5 min | 3.0 min (finding register) | **−1.5 min** |
| Domain screening entry (cognitive, motor, SE) | 4.0 min | 3.5 min (paper form fill) | **+0.5 min** |
| Risk result review + referral action | 0.5 min | 1.5 min (manual calculation) | **−1.0 min** |
| Sync confirmation (if online) | 0.2 min | 0.5 min (register filing) | **−0.3 min** |
| **Total per screening** | **~6.2 min** | **~8.5 min** | **−2.3 min (−27%)** |

> [!NOTE]
> The above is an estimate based on comparable mHealth deployment studies (ASHA mobile studies, ANMOL). A formal time-motion study must be conducted in Phase 7 pilot and results published in the Pilot Evaluation Report.

**Additional workload from sentinel sampling (D.2.2):**
- 5% of low/medium-flagged children require Supervisor re-review
- Estimated Supervisor time: 2–3 minutes per re-review
- At 200 screenings/month/block: ~10 re-reviews/month = ~20–30 min total Supervisor overhead

## 3.2 Data Consumption Model (Per AWW Device Per Month)

| Activity | Estimated Data Volume |
|---|---|
| Assessment submission (1 record, compressed) | ~4 KB |
| Risk result + SHAP fetch | ~2 KB |
| App update (monthly incremental) | ~8 MB |
| Dashboard sync (child list, 50 children) | ~15 KB |
| **Monthly total (100 screenings + app update)** | **~8.6 MB/month** |

This is compatible with a 1 GB/month mobile data plan. A 2G baseline of ~50 kbps can transfer one complete assessment in ≤ 2 seconds.

## 3.3 Storage Capacity Projection (5-Year Horizon)

Assumptions: 1 state; 50,000 Anganwadis; average 40 children per AWC; 2 screenings per year per child.

| Data Type | Per Record Size | Annual Records | Annual Storage | 5-Year Storage |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Child records | 2 KB | 2,000,000 | 4 GB | 20 GB |
| Assessment records | 5 KB | 4,000,000 | 20 GB | 100 GB |
| Risk results + SHAP | 3 KB | 4,000,000 | 12 GB | 60 GB |
| Trajectory rows | 0.5 KB | 4,000,000 | 2 GB | 10 GB |
| Audit log | 0.5 KB | ~20,000,000 | 10 GB | 50 GB |
| Model artifacts + reports | — | — | 5 GB | 15 GB |
| **Total (uncompressed)** | | | **~53 GB/year** | **~255 GB** |

With PostgreSQL compression and TimescaleDB compression (typically 5–10×), real storage need is approximately **30–60 GB over 5 years** for a single state at full scale.

**Infrastructure sizing recommendation:** 2× servers, 500 GB SSD each (RAID 1), with annual review. Object store (MinIO): 1 TB initially, reviewed at Year 2.

