> This is not a weakness — it is intellectual honesty that signals operational maturity.

## 4.2 Minimal Viable Phase 1 Architecture

For PoC, the system can run on a single Ubuntu 22.04 server (or VM) with:

```
Infrastructure (PoC only):
├── 1× Server: 8 vCPU, 16 GB RAM, 200 GB SSD
├── Docker Compose (no Kubernetes required at PoC)
│     ├── PostgreSQL 15 container
│     ├── FastAPI container (API + Risk Engine)
│     ├── Redis container (job queue)
│     ├── Celery worker container
│     └── Nginx container (TLS termination)
├── Android APK (sideloaded or via internal distribution)
└── React web app (static build served by Nginx)
```

This is deployable by 1 DevOps engineer in 1–2 days. The same Docker Compose can be lifted into Kubernetes for production scaling.

