# Cost Model Appendix

## Infrastructure Cost (Annual, NIC/Government Cloud or Equivalent)

### PoC / Pilot Stage (Year 1)

| Item | Spec | Estimated Annual Cost (INR) |
|---|---|---|
| Compute: Application server | 2× VMs, 8 vCPU / 16 GB RAM | ₹1,20,000 – ₹1,80,000 |
| Compute: Database server | 1× VM, 8 vCPU / 32 GB RAM, 500 GB SSD | ₹1,50,000 – ₹2,00,000 |
| Object storage (MinIO / NIC) | 1 TB | ₹15,000 – ₹30,000 |
| Network / egress | Internal NIC network (minimal cost) | ₹10,000 – ₹20,000 |
| SSL certificates, domain | — | ₹5,000 – ₹10,000 |
| **PoC Infrastructure Total** | | **₹3,00,000 – ₹4,40,000/year** |

### Production Stage (Year 2+, Single State)

| Item | Spec | Estimated Annual Cost (INR) |
|---|---|---|
| Compute cluster | 4–6 VMs (K8s nodes), 16 vCPU / 32 GB RAM each | ₹6,00,000 – ₹10,00,000 |
| Database (HA cluster) | 2× primary/replica, 32 GB RAM / 1 TB SSD | ₹4,00,000 – ₹6,00,000 |
| Object storage | 5 TB | ₹75,000 – ₹1,50,000 |
| Network, load balancer | — | ₹60,000 – ₹1,20,000 |
| Monitoring stack | Grafana Cloud OSS or self-hosted (minimal) | ₹0 – ₹30,000 |
| **Production Infrastructure Total** | | **₹11,35,000 – ₹18,00,000/year** |

> [!NOTE]
> If hosted on NIC Data Centre under empanelled rates (as recommended), actual costs may be 30–50% lower than market equivalents. These figures are reference estimates only; final costs depend on NIC/SDC rate card.

## Per-Child Operational Cost (Amortised)

At full state scale (50,000 AWCs, 40 children each, 2 screenings/year):

| Cost Category | Annual Cost (INR) | Per-Child Cost (INR) |
|---|---|---|
| Infrastructure (production) | ₹15,00,000 | ₹0.38 |
| O&M staffing (3 FTE technical) | ₹36,00,000 | ₹0.90 |
| Annual model retraining + audit | ₹5,00,000 | ₹0.13 |
| **Total per child screened per year** | | **~₹1.41** |

This cost per child is comparable to postage for a paper-based form system, making the economic case straightforward to present.

## Android Device Requirement Estimate (Pilot)

| Deployment | Devices Required | Recommended Spec | Unit Cost (INR) | Total (INR) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Pilot (50 AWWs) | 50 | Android 8+, 2 GB RAM, 16 GB storage | ₹6,000 – ₹8,000 | ₹3,00,000 – ₹4,00,000 |
| State scale (50,000 AWWs) | 50,000 | Same | ₹6,000 – ₹8,000 | ₹30 Cr – ₹40 Cr |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Many AWWs already use smartphones provided under government digitalisation schemes (e.g., POSHAN Tracker device procurement). Before budgeting for devices, audit what devices are already in field use in the target state. Real pilot cost may be zero for devices.

## 5-Year Total Cost of Ownership (Single State, Illustrative)

| Year | Infra | Staffing | Retraining/Audit | Misc | Total |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Y1 (PoC/Pilot) | ₹4,40,000 | ₹55,00,000 | ₹3,00,000 | ₹5,00,000 | **₹67,40,000** |
| Y2 (Production launch) | ₹15,00,000 | ₹50,00,000 | ₹8,00,000 | ₹3,00,000 | **₹76,00,000** |
| Y3 | ₹16,00,000 | ₹48,00,000 | ₹5,00,000 | ₹2,00,000 | **₹71,00,000** |
| Y4 (Tech refresh) | ₹18,00,000 | ₹48,00,000 | ₹8,00,000 | ₹5,00,000 | **₹79,00,000** |
| Y5 (Handover) | ₹16,00,000 | ₹40,00,000 | ₹5,00,000 | ₹8,00,000 | **₹69,00,000** |
| **5-Year Total** | **₹69,40,000** | **₹2,41,00,000** | **₹29,00,000** | **₹23,00,000** | **~₹3.62 Cr** |

At ₹1.41/child/year (with 4 million annual screenings at full scale): **total per-child cost over 5 years ≈ ₹7.05** — comparable to a single SMS notification per child per year, with far greater programme value.
